abstract: The closing passage in  President Donald Trump's impeachment-eve letter  to House Speaker Nancy Pelosi had the ring of truth to it. He was writing his thoughts for history, he said. For 100 years from now, "when people look back at this affair.”
snippet: The closing passage in  President Donald Trump's impeachment-eve letter  to House Speaker Nancy Pelosi had the ring of truth to it. He was writing his thoughts for history, he said. For 100 years from now, "when people look back at this affair.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The closing passage in President Donald Trump's impeachment-eve letter to House Speaker Nancy Pelosi had the ring of truth to it. He was writing his thoughts for history, he said. For 100 years from now, "when people look back at this affair.”
headline_main: AP FACT CHECK: Trump's Flawed Impeachment Letter to Pelosi
headline_print_headline: AP FACT CHECK: Trump's Flawed Impeachment Letter to Pelosi

abstract: The death was the 20th of a service member during combat operations this year.
snippet: The death was the 20th of a service member during combat operations this year.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — An American service member was killed in Afghanistan on Monday, according to military officials, bringing to 20 the number of troops who have died during combat operations this year.

abstract: Shares were mostly lower Monday in quiet trading ahead of Christmas holidays for many markets.

lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Shares were mostly lower Monday in quiet trading ahead of Christmas holidays for many markets.
headline_main: World Shares Mostly Lower in Quiet Pre-Christmas Trading
headline_print_headline: World Shares Mostly Lower in Quiet Pre-Christmas Trading

abstract: The leaders of China, Japan and South Korea are holding a trilateral summit in China this week amid feuds over trade, military maneuverings and historical animosities. Most striking has been a complex dispute between Seoul and Tokyo, while Beijing has recently sought to tone down its disagreements with its two neighbors.
snippet: The leaders of China, Japan and South Korea are holding a trilateral summit in China this week amid feuds over trade, military maneuverings and historical animosities. Most striking has been a complex dispute between Seoul and Tokyo, while Beijing...
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — The leaders of China, Japan and South Korea are holding a trilateral summit in China this week amid feuds over trade, military maneuverings and historical animosities. Most striking has been a complex dispute between Seoul and Tokyo, while Beijing has recently sought to tone down its disagreements with its two neighbors.
headline_main: China, South Korea, Japan Meet Over Trade, Regional Disputes
headline_print_headline: China, South Korea, Japan Meet Over Trade, Regional Disputes

abstract: With lawmakers at odds over a trial’s format, impeachment proceedings are in limbo.
snippet: With lawmakers at odds over a trial’s format, impeachment proceedings are in limbo.
lead_paragraph: Top Democrats on Sunday renewed their demands for witnesses to testify at President Trump’s impeachment trial, citing newly released emails showing that the White House asked officials to keep quiet over the suspension of military aid to Ukraine just 90 minutes after Mr. Trump leaned on that country’s president to investigate former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr.

abstract: Members of Congress should not be allowed to buy and sell stocks, or to serve on corporate boards.
snippet: Members of Congress should not be allowed to buy and sell stocks, or to serve on corporate boards.
lead_paragraph: The case of Chris Collins, the New York Republican who resigned from Congress and pleaded guilty to insider trading earlier this fall, was a rare victory in the long-running battle to ensure that members of Congress do not take improper advantage of their privileged positions.

abstract: The media has a bigger problem than liberal bias.
snippet: The media has a bigger problem than liberal bias.
lead_paragraph: John F. Harris is about as mainstream as the mainstream media gets. He spent 21 years at The Washington Post, including as its political editor. Then he became the founding editor of Politico, where he is now a columnist.

headline_main: How ‘Centrist Bias’ Hurts Sanders and Warren

abstract: Evangelicals continue to support Trump in overwhelming numbers.
snippet: Evangelicals continue to support Trump in overwhelming numbers.
lead_paragraph: Thursday night, Christianity Today, long known as the “flagship” magazine of American evangelicalism, broke the internet with an editorial arguing for the impeachment and removal of Donald Trump from office. The piece, penned by the magazine’s outgoing editor, Mark Galli, implored evangelicals to consider the “unambiguous facts” of the impeachment case against the president, maintaining his actions not only violated the Constitution, but were also “profoundly immoral.”

headline_main: That Christianity Today Editorial Won’t Change Anything

abstract: With Israel’s prime minister under indictment, Gideon Saar is challenging him for the Likud party leadership. His chances may be slim, but he has cracked Likud’s united front.
snippet: With Israel’s prime minister under indictment, Gideon Saar is challenging him for the Likud party leadership. His chances may be slim, but he has cracked Likud’s united front.
lead_paragraph: OR YEHUDA, Israel — With Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel politically weakened and steeped in legal troubles, a rival from within his conservative Likud party has emerged to challenge his grip on the party leadership.
